the teacher today.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.319
Teach us, Morty!

01:51.403 --> 01:52.570
Interesting.

01:52.654 --> 01:54.030
W-w-w-what do you
want me to teach you?

01:54.114 --> 01:55.156
Ooh, ooh!

01:55.240 --> 01:56.991
How do you make
concentrated dark matter?

01:57.075 --> 01:58.242
Oh, that's a good question.

01:58.327 --> 01:59.660
Concentrated huh?

01:59.745 --> 02:00.870
Concentrated dark matter...

02:00.954 --> 02:03.456
the fuel for accelerated
space travel.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.540
Now, do you know how to make it?

02:04.625 --> 02:05.500
Umm...

02:05.584 --> 02:06.584
JESSICA:
Come on, Morty.

02:06.585 --> 02:08.753
Isn't your grandpa,
like, a scientist?

02:08.837 --> 02:11.380
Oh, yeah, but, you know,
he told me that I shouldn't go

02:11.465 --> 02:14.091
around spouting off about, you
know, his science and stuff.

02:14.176 --> 02:17.178
I bet you've seen him make
concentrated dark matter a lot.

02:17.262 --> 02:20.431
You know, if you tell us,
I'll be your girlfriend.

02:20.516 --> 02:21.599
Uh, y-you will?

02:21.683 --> 02:23.601
Seems like a rare opportunity,
Morty.

02:23.685 --> 02:24.977
