03:56.612 --> 03:57.612
[ whirring]

03:57.613 --> 03:58.613
You can do this.

03:58.614 --> 03:59.655
How did this happen?!

03:59.740 --> 04:01.157
Where's the
Abductions Department?

04:01.241 --> 04:03.784
Hey, man, Abductions just
follows the acquisition order.

04:03.869 --> 04:05.286
Don't put this on Acquisitions!

04:05.370 --> 04:07.914
We only acquire humans that
haven't been simulated!

04:07.998 --> 04:10.708
Well, simulations doesn't
simulate anybody that's been

04:10.792 --> 04:12.919
abducted,
so [chuckles] oh, I see!

04:13.003 --> 04:14.295
Oh, oh!
It was no one's fault.

04:14.379 --> 04:15.546
Oh, okay. [ chuckles ]

04:15.631 --> 04:16.797
I'm sorry.
Well, then, problem solved.

04:16.882 --> 04:17.924
Oh, wait... no.

04:18.008 --> 04:19.967
There's still another
human in here!

04:20.052 --> 04:21.385
Who is he?

04:21.470 --> 04:22.970
Rick's son-in-law,
Jerry Smith.

04:23.055 --> 04:25.848
So far, he hasn't noticed
he's in a simulation.

04:25.933 --> 04:26.933
[ sighs ]

04:27.017 --> 04:28.497
Well, cap his sector at 5%
processing,

04:28.560 --> 04:30.686
keep his settings on auto, and
we'll deal with him later.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.897
Rick Sanchez is the target.

04:35.484 --> 04:36.484
[ inhales deeply ] Got to relax.

04:36.568 --> 04:37.860
It's just a pitch.

04:37.945 --> 04:39.195
Got to relax.

04:39.279 --> 04:40.071
[ click ]

04:40.155 --> 04:40.988
[ static ]

04:41.073 --> 04:42.531
This is Earth radio.

04:42.616 --> 04:45.242
And now, here's... human music.

04:45.327 --> 04:48.454
[ repetitive rhythmic beeping]

04:48.538 --> 04:50.456
Hmm. Human music.

04:50.540 --> 04:53.000
I like it.

04:53.085 --> 04:55.002
[ beeping continues]

05:02.844 --> 05:06.013
[ Rick and Morty panting ]

05:06.098 --> 05:07.098
Rick!

05:07.099 --> 05:08.182
Uhp, uhp, uhp!

05:08.266 --> 05:09.558
Morty, keep your hands
off your ding-dong!

05:09.643 --> 05:11.123
It's the only way
we can speak freely.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.353
Look around you, Morty.

05:12.437 --> 05:14.480
Do you really think
this [burps] world is real?

05:14.564 --> 05:17.149
You'd have to be an idiot not to
notice all the sloppy details.

05:17.234 --> 05:19.360
Look... that guy's putting
a bun between two hot dogs.

05:19.444 --> 05:20.486
MORTY:
I don't know, Rick.

05:20.570 --> 05:22.029
I mean, I've seen people
do that before.

05:22.114 --> 05:23.434
RICK:
Well, look at that old lady.

05:23.448 --> 05:25.074
She's... she's walking
a cat on a leash.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.076
Uh, Mrs. Spencer does
that all the time, Rick.

05:27.160 --> 05:29.495
Look, I-I-l don't want to
hear about Mrs. Spencer, Morty!

05:29.579 --> 05:30.663
She's an idiot!

05:30.747 --> 05:31.622
All right, all right, there.

05:31.707 --> 05:32.873
W-what about that, Morty?

05:32.958 --> 05:34.709
MORTY:
Okay, okay, you got me on that one.

05:34.793 --> 05:35.918
Oh, really, Morty?

05:36.003 --> 05:37.461
Are you sure you haven't
seen that somewhere

05:37.546 --> 05:38.421
in real life before?

05:38.505 --> 05:39.755
No, no.
I haven't seen that.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.799
I mean, why would a
pop tart want to live inside

05:41.883 --> 05:43.217
a toaster, Rick?

05:43.301 --> 05:45.678
I mean, that would be, like, the
scariest place for them to live.

05:45.762 --> 05:46.804
You know what I mean?

05:46.888 --> 05:48.128
You're missing the point, Morty.

05:48.140 --> 05:50.060
Why would he drive a smaller
toaster with wheels?

05:50.142 --> 05:52.662
I mean, does your car look like
a smaller version of your house?

05:52.728 --> 05:53.769
No.

05:53.854 --> 05:54.854
So, why are they doing this?

05:54.938 --> 05:56.022
W-what do they want?

05:56.106 --> 05:57.189
Well, that would be
obvious to you, Morty,

05:57.274 --> 05:58.514
if you'd been paying attention.

05:58.567 --> 05:59.734
[ siren wails ]

05:59.818 --> 06:01.068
[ tires screech ]

06:01.153 --> 06:02.987
We got the President of the
United States in here!

06:03.071 --> 06:05.906
We need 10cc of concentrated
dark matter, stat, or he'll die!

06:05.991 --> 06:07.950
Concentrated dark matter?

06:08.035 --> 06:09.660
They were asking
about that in class.

06:09.745 --> 06:11.412
Yeah, it's a special fuel I
invented to travel through

06:11.496 --> 06:13.122
space faster than anybody else.

06:13.206 --> 06:15.374
These Zigerions are always
trying to scam me out of my secrets,

06:15.459 --> 06:18.002
but they made a big
mistake this time, Morty.

06:18.086 --> 06:19.879
They dragged you into this.

06:19.963 --> 06:21.047
Now they're gonna pay!

06:21.131 --> 06:22.691
What do you...
w-w-what are we gonna do?

06:22.758 --> 06:24.675
We'll scam the scammers, Morty.

06:24.760 --> 06:27.470
And we're gonna take them for
everything they've got.

06:27.554 --> 06:30.181
JERRY:
National Apple Farmers of America,

06:30.265 --> 06:32.349
welcome to our Ad Agency.

06:32.434 --> 06:34.351
I'm Jerry Smith.

06:35.479 --> 06:36.479
All right.

06:36.480 --> 06:37.855
I'll just... get to the pitch.

06:37.939 --> 06:41.901
Um, simple question, gentlemen,
[ hoarsely ] what are apples?

06:41.985 --> 06:43.319
[ clears throat ] Excuse me.

06:43.403 --> 06:45.112
Ahh.

06:45.197 --> 06:47.239
[ coughs, clears throat ]

06:47.324 --> 06:49.200
What are apples?

06:49.284 --> 06:51.869
Apples are food.

06:51.953 --> 06:54.455
And... when do we need food?

06:54.539 --> 06:56.415
When we're hungry.

06:57.584 --> 07:00.544
With that, I give
you your new slogan!

07:00.629 --> 07:02.129
[ sighs ]

07:02.214 --> 07:04.048
Well, say something!

07:04.132 --> 07:05.132
Do you like it?

07:05.217 --> 07:06.258
Yes.

07:06.343 --> 07:07.343
You do?

07:07.344 --> 07:08.385
ALL:
Yes.

07:08.470 --> 07:10.012
So... I sold it?

07:10.097 --> 07:12.014
[ laughs ] I sold the idea?

07:12.099 --> 07:13.099
ALL:
Yes.

07:13.141 --> 07:14.767
Oh, my god! Thank you!

07:14.851 --> 07:16.727
TOGETHER:
Thank you.

07:16.812 --> 07:17.812
You're welcome.

07:17.813 --> 07:20.815
[ "Baker Street" plays ]

07:22.109 --> 07:23.234
Hey!

07:23.318 --> 07:24.693
I just sold my first pitch!

07:24.778 --> 07:26.153
[ dialing ]

07:26.238 --> 07:27.363
Slow down! Lookin' good.

07:27.447 --> 07:28.531
My man!

07:28.615 --> 07:31.242
[ beeping, telephone ringing ]

07:31.326 --> 07:32.451
