10:44.102 --> 10:46.312
but they're reallygood
at making these chips.

10:47.731 --> 10:49.231
RICK: I've got so many,
l can barely hold them all.

10:49.316 --> 10:50.316
[ chuckles ]

10:50.317 --> 10:51.317
Look at...
look at this.

10:51.401 --> 10:52.401
Oops. l dropped one.

10:52.444 --> 10:53.777
Don't worry about it, Morty.

10:53.862 --> 10:55.279
There's plenty of them,
you little goofball.

10:55.363 --> 10:56.405
[ both laugh ]

10:56.489 --> 10:58.032
Come here, Morty!
Oh, l gotcha!

10:58.116 --> 10:58.991
Come on, quit it, Rick!

10:59.075 --> 11:00.367
Quit it!
[ laughs ]

11:00.452 --> 11:02.369
Nothing wrong with just a
little bit of horseplay every

11:02.454 --> 11:03.996
now and then, little fella.

11:08.501 --> 11:09.543
[ glass shatters ]

11:15.759 --> 11:16.967
Wow. What do you know?

11:17.052 --> 11:18.385
Huh. That was easy.

11:18.470 --> 11:20.888
Totes malotes, dawg.

11:20.972 --> 11:22.097
Just kind of hard to believe,
you know?

11:22.182 --> 11:23.557
Believe it, Morty.

11:23.641 --> 11:25.851
And once again, I'm flying away
with everything l can carry,

11:25.935 --> 11:28.354
and the Zigerions
got nothing of mine.

11:33.735 --> 11:34.526
[ sighs ]

11:34.611 --> 11:35.851
Mr. Marklevitz,
do you have a...

11:35.904 --> 11:37.029
minute to talk?

11:37.113 --> 11:38.489
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

11:38.573 --> 11:40.157
Look, I'm a fraud.

11:40.241 --> 11:41.700
I mean, let's face it...

11:41.785 --> 11:44.203
"Hungry For Apples" is just
a rip-off of "Got Milk?"

11:44.287 --> 11:45.496
It's almost identical.

11:45.580 --> 11:46.789
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

11:46.873 --> 11:48.082
[ sighs ] Okay.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.333
I deserve that.

11:49.417 --> 11:52.711
Umm... I guess...
I'll just pack up my desk.

11:52.796 --> 11:54.004
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

11:54.089 --> 11:56.757
[ crying ]

11:56.841 --> 11:59.426
[ sobbing ] Oh, my God.

11:59.511 --> 12:02.054
Wait. You know what?! No!

12:02.138 --> 12:04.139
The milk people don't
have a patent on

12:04.224 --> 12:06.100
simple rhetorical questions!

12:06.184 --> 12:08.644
There's not even a single word
in "Hungry For Apples" that's

12:08.728 --> 12:10.521
shared by "Got Milk?"

12:10.605 --> 12:12.439
It's a completely
different slogan.

12:12.524 --> 12:13.816
It's different!

12:13.900 --> 12:15.818
And I shouldn't be fired.

12:15.902 --> 12:17.528
I should be promoted!

12:17.612 --> 12:18.852
- [ snaps fingers ] Yes.
- Yeah!

12:18.863 --> 12:19.863
Wait. Really?

12:19.906 --> 12:20.948
- [ snaps fingers ] Yes.
- Yes!

12:21.032 --> 12:22.574
I mean, I'm...
it may be derivative,

12:22.659 --> 12:24.451
but it's the most successful
campaign to come out of this

12:24.536 --> 12:25.536
agency in a long time.

12:25.537 --> 12:26.954
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

12:27.038 --> 12:28.956
I-I'm not saying it should win
an award for commercials,

12:29.040 --> 12:31.041
but it could certainly be
nominated for an award

12:31.126 --> 12:33.001
for commercials specifically
about apples,

12:33.086 --> 12:34.711
like... an Appley or something.

12:34.796 --> 12:35.796
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

12:35.880 --> 12:36.922
Is there really an
award called the Appley

12:37.006 --> 12:38.132
for Apple-Related ad campaigns?

12:38.216 --> 12:39.258
[ snaps fingers ] Yes.

12:39.342 --> 12:40.551
- Could we nominate me?
- [ snaps fingers ] Yes.

12:40.635 --> 12:42.386
Holy crap!

12:42.470 --> 12:43.470
[ beeping ]

12:48.268 --> 12:49.685
Get in, Morty.

12:49.769 --> 12:52.354
I'm gonna [burps] be able to use
these processors to make some

12:52.439 --> 12:54.148
real important science stuff.

12:55.275 --> 12:56.608
[ keypad beeping ]

12:56.693 --> 12:57.901
Huh.

12:57.986 --> 12:59.153
I thought l entered
the code right.

12:59.237 --> 13:00.487
[ keypad beeping ]

13:07.454 --> 13:08.954
Wha... well, what's this?

13:09.038 --> 13:11.498
W-what could this possibly be?

13:11.583 --> 13:14.168
Because it looks like
you're inside a simulation...

13:14.252 --> 13:17.087
inside a simulation.

13:17.172 --> 13:18.714
You're still on the ship.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.340
Game-day bucket go boom.

13:20.425 --> 13:22.926
Sir, the, uh, doctor's
appointment to examine the

13:23.011 --> 13:25.095
discoloration on your
butthole flaps was...

13:25.180 --> 13:26.513
Too loud, Cynthia.

13:26.598 --> 13:27.764
Too loud and too specific.

13:27.849 --> 13:28.849
Uhh...

13:28.850 --> 13:29.975
[ chuckles ]

13:30.059 --> 13:31.852
We've known how to make
concentrated dark matter

13:31.936 --> 13:33.896
for a long time.

13:33.980 --> 13:39.401
But now we also know the code to
your fabled safe, Rick Sanchez!

13:39.486 --> 13:42.988
All your most valuable
secrets will now be ours!

13:43.072 --> 13:44.740
Uh, yeah, until I get home
before you and change the

13:44.824 --> 13:46.325
combination,
you bunch of idiots!

13:46.409 --> 13:47.743
That is why you're
never getting home.

13:47.827 --> 13:48.952
Get them!

13:49.037 --> 13:50.329
[ grunts ]

13:50.413 --> 13:52.498
[ aliens shouting, groaning ]

13:52.582 --> 13:55.417
Run, Morty!

13:55.502 --> 13:57.377
[ both panting ]

14:02.634 --> 14:04.468
Oh, my God!

14:08.848 --> 14:10.224
[ beep, click ]

14:13.728 --> 14:16.188
[ mechanical breathing ]

14:20.985 --> 14:21.985
Ow!

14:25.782 --> 14:26.615
[ click, whoosh ]

14:26.699 --> 14:29.034
[ aliens screaming ]

14:29.118 --> 14:31.036
[ both panting ]

14:31.120 --> 14:32.246
l got to tell you, this morning,

14:32.330 --> 14:33.810
l didn't even know
this award existed.

14:33.873 --> 14:35.332
Now I'm holding one.

14:35.416 --> 14:37.709
And... um...

14:37.794 --> 14:41.547
look, I want to say that today
was the best day of my life...

14:41.631 --> 14:45.759
but... the truth is, it's...
it's more meaningful than that.

14:45.843 --> 14:46.843
MAN:
My man!

14:46.886 --> 14:48.136
Yes. Thank you, sir.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.013
[ sighs deeply ]

14:50.098 --> 14:53.684
l...am... finally complete!

14:53.768 --> 14:55.352
[ beeping ]

14:56.604 --> 14:59.189
My... my... my... my man!

15:02.193 --> 15:03.610
Aah!

15:03.695 --> 15:04.945
What the hell?!

15:05.029 --> 15:08.240
[ beeping ]

15:08.324 --> 15:09.449
No.

15:09.534 --> 15:10.534
- Jerry?!
- Dad!

15:10.535 --> 15:11.994
What are you doing here?

15:12.078 --> 15:13.161
W-why are you
dressed like a waiter?

15:13.246 --> 15:14.371
Screw it.
We don't have time.

15:14.455 --> 15:15.247
Come on.

15:15.331 --> 15:16.748
[ sobbing ] No!

15:23.256 --> 15:25.215
[ alarm blaring ]

15:25.300 --> 15:26.300
Ohhhhh!

15:28.386 --> 15:29.553
[ beeping ] Aah!

15:49.115 --> 15:51.491
ALL:
Yes! Yes! Yes!

15:59.626 --> 16:00.626
Oof!

16:01.836 --> 16:03.253
Man up, Jerry!

16:03.338 --> 16:04.713
I may need you to
work the lasers.

16:04.797 --> 16:06.632
[ beeping ]

16:07.884 --> 16:08.675
[ slurps ]

16:08.760 --> 16:09.593
[ gasps ]

16:09.677 --> 16:11.553
[ alarm blaring ]

16:17.393 --> 16:19.227
Oh, man!
They're hot on our tail, Rick!

16:19.312 --> 16:21.271
I guess they really do have
concentrated dark matter.

16:21.356 --> 16:22.856
Well, you know how to make it,
too, right, Rick?

16:22.940 --> 16:23.940
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

16:24.025 --> 16:25.317
Uh, check the engine room.

16:25.401 --> 16:28.070
We just need Cesium, Plutonic
Quarks, and bottled water.

16:30.573 --> 16:31.573
It's all here, Rick!

16:31.658 --> 16:32.658
Wow, Morty.
Lucky break.

16:32.742 --> 16:33.909
Grab that bucket.

16:33.993 --> 16:37.162
Okay, two parts Plutonic Quarks,
one part Cesium.

16:37.246 --> 16:38.372
Okay. Uh-huh.

16:39.749 --> 16:40.624
[ fizzing ]

16:40.708 --> 16:41.875
All right.

16:41.959 --> 16:43.460
Now empty the water bottle
into the bucket and pour

16:43.544 --> 16:46.546
it all into the fuel tank so we
can get the hell out of here!

16:46.631 --> 16:47.711
What are you doing, Morty?!

16:47.757 --> 16:48.757
There's no time!

16:48.841 --> 16:50.801
[ beeping ]

16:53.721 --> 16:55.305
[ stammering ]

16:55.390 --> 16:57.057
Oh, no.

16:57.141 --> 16:58.266
What the...

16:58.351 --> 16:59.351
No!

16:59.435 --> 17:01.103
[ laughter ]

17:04.607 --> 17:06.733
Oh, my God, Rick.

17:06.818 --> 17:08.485
How dumb are you?

17:08.569 --> 17:10.237
You're inside a simulation...

17:10.321 --> 17:12.322
of a simulation...

17:12.407 --> 17:15.117
inside another giant simulation!

17:15.201 --> 17:16.493
[ laughs ]

17:16.577 --> 17:19.329
W-We never had the recipe for
concentrated dark matter.

17:19.414 --> 17:20.997
But we do now!

17:21.082 --> 17:22.708
We do now, sucka!

17:22.792 --> 17:24.918
You simulated my
grandson's genitalia?!

17:25.002 --> 17:27.421
Y-Y-You bunch of
diabolical sons of bitches!

17:27.505 --> 17:29.798
Kevin fought real hard to
supervise that project.

17:29.882 --> 17:31.883
You said you weren't
gonna tell anyone!

17:31.968 --> 17:33.760
I'm never gonna live
this down, am I?

17:33.845 --> 17:35.137
All right. Okay.
All right, great. Wonderful.

17:35.221 --> 17:36.680
You win.
Can we go home now?

17:36.764 --> 17:38.390
I don't know.
Can you?

17:38.474 --> 17:39.349
Ha! Nice.

17:39.434 --> 17:41.017
Okay, okay.

17:41.102 --> 17:43.061
Show this gullible
turd to his shuttle.

17:43.146 --> 17:44.438
I'm done with him.

17:44.522 --> 17:45.439
Oh, wait.
Let me get a picture.

17:45.523 --> 17:46.356
[ shutter clicks ]

17:46.441 --> 17:47.941
Aww. Look at his face.

17:48.025 --> 17:50.225
He's trying to figure out if
he's in a simulation still.

17:50.236 --> 17:51.236
Are you, Rick?

17:51.279 --> 17:52.612
Are you?

17:52.697 --> 17:53.739
[ laughs ]

17:53.823 --> 17:55.031
You're not.

17:55.116 --> 17:57.075
Or are you?

17:59.078 --> 18:01.997
Oh, a-and, by the way, l don't
have discolored butthole flaps.

18:02.081 --> 18:03.415
That was part of the simulation.

18:03.499 --> 18:04.583
Oh.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.126
Uh, sir, should I cancel
that appointment, then?

18:06.210 --> 18:07.669
Yeah! Of course you should!

18:07.754 --> 18:08.879
[ chuckles ]

18:08.963 --> 18:10.005
No, keep it.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.369
Move it up, actually,
if you can.

18:16.179 --> 18:17.471
RICK:
Hey, Jerry, don't worry about it.

18:17.555 --> 18:19.264
So what if the most meaningful
day of your life was a

18:19.348 --> 18:21.808
simulation operating at
minimum cap[burps]acity?

18:21.893 --> 18:23.268
You know what, Rick?

18:23.352 --> 18:25.562
Those guys took you
for a ride, too.

18:25.646 --> 18:27.689
You should try having a little
respect for the dummies of the Universe,

18:27.774 --> 18:29.566
now that you're one of us.

18:29.650 --> 18:31.067
Maybe you're right, Jerry.

18:31.152 --> 18:32.861
Maybe you're right.

18:32.945 --> 18:34.237
[ aliens cheering ]

18:34.322 --> 18:36.573
[ dance music plays ]
All right, everybody.

18:36.657 --> 18:40.118
Two parts Plutonic Quarks...

18:40.203 --> 18:42.412
One part Cesium...

18:42.497 --> 18:43.705
[ fizzing ]

18:43.790 --> 18:45.957
A-and listen,
I'm sorry for yelling earlier.

18:46.042 --> 18:48.418
I-I couldn't ask
for a better staff.

18:48.503 --> 18:51.838
I love you guys,
and I love all your families.

18:51.923 --> 18:55.050
And the final ingredient...

18:57.512 --> 18:58.595
JERRY:
Whoa!

18:58.679 --> 19:00.680
What the hell?!
W-what happened back there?

19:00.765 --> 19:03.308
Why don't you ask the smartest
people in the Universe, Jerry?

19:03.392 --> 19:05.185
Oh, yeah.
[ burps ] you can't.

19:05.269 --> 19:06.603
They blew up.

19:06.687 --> 19:08.146
[ sighs ]

19:08.231 --> 19:09.272
[ beep ]

19:09.357 --> 19:12.484
[ "Baker Street" plays]

19:12.568 --> 19:15.403
[ vocalizing ]

19:16.405 --> 19:21.451
[ vocalizing out of sync ]

19:27.458 --> 19:30.836
[ "Baker Street" continues ]

19:46.978 --> 19:48.103
JERRY:
So...

19:48.187 --> 19:49.688
what do you think?

19:50.690 --> 19:51.481
You're fired.

19:51.566 --> 19:52.691
Wha...

19:52.775 --> 19:55.777
But t-this idea was tested in a
state-of-the-art simulation.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.487
Well, then, it was
a terrible simulation.

19:57.572 --> 19:59.072
Get out.

20:00.992 --> 20:02.367
[ door opens, closes ]

20:02.451 --> 20:05.871
Man, how does a guy like that go
home and have sex with his wife?

20:06.747 --> 20:07.581
Hey, Morty.

20:07.665 --> 20:08.498
What?

20:08.583 --> 20:09.583
Hey, little buddy.

20:09.625 --> 20:11.418
H-h-how you doing
in here right now?

20:11.502 --> 20:13.378
Aw, geez, Rick.
What are you doing, man?

20:13.462 --> 20:14.838
Y-y-you're a
good kid, Morty.

20:14.922 --> 20:16.923
Y-you're a real l-little
c-character, Morty.

20:17.008 --> 20:18.258
Oh, boy.

20:18.342 --> 20:20.886
You know, l had a really
rocky road today, M-Morty.

20:20.970 --> 20:23.013
You're my little friend,
aren't you?

20:23.097 --> 20:24.222
[ sighs ]

20:24.307 --> 20:26.433
We had some good times together,
huh, M-Morty?

20:26.517 --> 20:28.560
We... you're a real
true hero out in the field.

20:28.644 --> 20:31.771
You're a Li... you're a real
trooper, huh, M-M-Morty?

20:31.856 --> 20:33.016
Have you been drinking, Rick?

20:33.024 --> 20:34.274
I really appreciate you, Morty.

20:34.358 --> 20:35.692
O-okay, cool.

20:35.776 --> 20:37.444
A-all right, Rick...
you little son of a bitch!

20:37.528 --> 20:39.362
Y-y... are you a simulation?!

20:39.447 --> 20:40.739
Huh?! Are you a simulation?!

20:40.823 --> 20:42.282
No! No! No!

20:42.366 --> 20:43.533
You little son of a bitch!

20:43.618 --> 20:44.618
[ gasping ]

20:44.660 --> 20:46.244
l-I-I'm sorry, Morty.

20:46.329 --> 20:47.537
Y-you're a good...
you're a good kid, Morty.

20:47.622 --> 20:48.705
Geez!

20:48.789 --> 20:49.873
Y-you're a good...
you're a good kid.

20:49.957 --> 20:51.041
Oh, my god!

20:51.125 --> 20:52.125
[ snoring ]

20:52.168 --> 20:54.711
W-W-What the hell?

20:54.795 --> 20:55.795
What a life.

20:57.590 --> 20:58.965
Did you get any of that?

20:59.050 --> 21:00.884
It's a good-a show!
